# üç∫ Nordic Thunder ‚Äì HBC 1019 DIPA (20L Braumeister Version, 18‚Äì20¬∞C Fermentation)

## Target Stats
- **OG**: ~1.072
- **FG**: ~1.012‚Äì1.014
- **ABV**: ~7.7‚Äì7.9%
- **IBU**: ~40
- **SRM**: ~5 (hazy golden)

---

## Adjusted Grain Bill (Braumeister-friendly)

| Grain                   | Amount | %    |
|-------------------------|--------|------|
| Pale Ale Malt           | 4.5 kg | 64%  |
| Flaked Oats             | 1.2 kg | 17%  |
| Wheat Malt              | 0.8 kg | 11%  |
| Carapils/Dextrine       | 0.3 kg | 4%   |
| Acidulated Malt         | 0.2 kg | 3%   |
| Table Sugar (late boil) | 300g   | ‚Äî    |

---

## Water Profile (recommended)

- **Ca**: 100‚Äì120 ppm
- **Mg**: 10 ppm
- **Cl**: 150 ppm
- **SO‚ÇÑ**: 50 ppm

Adjust with **CaCl‚ÇÇ** and **gypsum** to suit.

---

## Hop Schedule (~40 IBU total)

| Hop         | Amount | Time                         | IBU  | Notes                     |
|-------------|--------|------------------------------|------|--------------------------|
| Magnum      | 10g    | 60 min (during boil)         | ~20  | Clean bittering           |
| HBC 1019    | 30g    | Whirlpool\* @ 75‚Äì80¬∞C, 20 min | ~10  | Core fruit/berry          |
| El Dorado   | 30g    | Whirlpool\* @ 75‚Äì80¬∞C, 20 min | ~10  | Amplifies tropical/pear   |
| HBC 1019    | 60g    | Dry hop (Day 4‚Äì5)             | ‚Äî    | Biotransformation         |
| HBC 1019    | 60g    | Dry hop (Day 8‚Äì9, post-fermentation) | ‚Äî    | Bold finish               |
| Mosaic/Citra (optional) | 30g | Whirlpool\*/dry hop  | ‚Äî    | Added complexity          |

\* Manual stir if no whirlpool.

---

## Braumeister Process

### Mash Schedule

| Step              | Temp   | Time  |
|-------------------|--------|-------|
| Dough-in          | 50¬∞C   | 10 min |
| Beta-amylase rest | 66¬∞C   | 60 min |
| Mash-out          | 75¬∞C   | 10 min |

1. **Fill Braumeister with ~25‚Äì26L of water** (account for boil-off and losses).
2. Add minerals to water before heating.
3. Insert malt pipe and grain bill slowly, stir to avoid dough balls.
4. Run mash program as above.

### Lauter / Sparge

- Remove malt pipe after mash-out.
- Rinse grain with ~3‚Äì4L of 75¬∞C water to top up to pre-boil volume (~26L).

### Boil (90 min recommended)

- Boil vigorously for 90 min ‚Üí improves haze stability in NEIPAs.
- Add **Magnum at 60 min**.
- At 10 min left:
  - Add kettle finings (optional; some NEIPA brewers skip).
- At flameout:
  - Cool to **75‚Äì80¬∞C**.
  - Add **HBC 1019 + El Dorado** ‚Üí steep for 20 min.

### Sugar Addition

- Add **300g table sugar** after boil ‚Üí fully dissolve during whirlpool or at flameout.

### Cooling

- Chill to **18‚Äì20¬∞C**.
- Transfer to fermenter.

---

## Fermentation

### Yeast

- **Mangrove Jack‚Äôs M12 Kveik** (1 sachet, no starter required).

### Schedule

1. **Pitch yeast at 18‚Äì20¬∞C**.
2. Maintain temp for **7‚Äì10 days** (longer at low temp).
3. On **Day 4‚Äì5**, add **first dry hop (60g HBC 1019)** at high activity (or near end of primary).
4. On **Day 8‚Äì9**, add **second dry hop (60g HBC 1019)** post-fermentation.
5. Optional:
    - Cold crash to 4‚Äì5¬∞C for 2‚Äì3 days (if kegging).
    - Skip cold crash if bottling and aiming to preserve max hop aroma.

---

## Packaging

- Aim for **~2.5 vol CO‚ÇÇ** for this style (moderately high carbonation).
- Minimize O‚ÇÇ exposure:
    - Purge keg.
    - If bottling, bottle carefully and promptly after final dry hop.

---

## Final Notes (Braumeister + 18‚Äì20¬∞C fermentation)

‚úÖ M12 will ferment slower and cleaner at this range ‚Üí more hop-driven IPA.  
‚úÖ Adjust dry hop timing slightly to match fermentation speed.  
‚úÖ Keep whirlpool additions *below 80¬∞C* ‚Üí preserves fruit character.  
‚úÖ If you have a **hop spider or bag**, use it for the dry hops to ease post-fermentation handling.

